biz.gabrys.easybundle

Interface BundleManager

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    BundleManagerImpl

    public interface BundleManager

    Responsible for the management of bundles (returning and changing locale). Also contains methods to manage listeners which will be informed about the bundles changes.

    How to use the manager:

    1. Define correct interface for the bundle: 
       public interface Messages {
 
     String getTitle();
 }
      To check whether the interface is correct you can add a JUnit test: 
       public final MessagesTest {
      
      @Test
      public void isCorrectInterface() {
         BundleValidator.validateInterface(Messages.class);
      }
 }
    2. Create a new instance of BundleManager (e.g. BundleManagerImpl) with specified implementation of BundleFactory (e.g. MultiplePropertyResourceBundleFactory) - before define translations in accordance with the guidelines of the factory: 
       final BundleFactory factory = new MultiplePropertyResourceBundleFactory();
 final BundleManager manager = new BundleManagerImpl(factory);

      For simplicity, we use MultiplePropertyResourceBundleManagerStorage.

    3. Get the bundle and register listener: 
       public class FrameImpl extends Frame implements BundleReloadListener {
      private static final Messages BUNDLE =
          MultiplePropertyResourceBundleManagerStorage.getManager().getBundle(Messages.class);
       
      public FrameImpl() {
          MultiplePropertyResourceBundleManagerStorage.getManager().register(this);
          onBundleReload();
      }
      
      public void onBundleReload() {
          this.setTitle(BUNDLE.getTitle());
      }
      
      public void destroy() {
          MultiplePropertyResourceBundleManagerStorage.getManager().unregister(this);
      }
 }
    4. Now you can change the locale of displayed frame: 
       final Frame frame = new FrameImpl();
 frame.show();
 // change to english
 MultiplePropertyResourceBundleManagerStorage.getManager().setLocale(Locale.ENGLISH));
 // do something...
 
 // change to polish
 MultiplePropertyResourceBundleManagerStorage.getManager().setLocale(new Locale("pl"));
 // do something...
    Since:
    1.0
    See Also:
    BundleFactory, BundleValidator, MultiplePropertyResourceBundleFactory, PropertyResourceBundleFactory

        Sets a new locale for all bundles (those created and which will be created) and after the successful set - reload all listeners.
        Parameters:
        locale - the new locale.
        Throws:
        ReloadBundleException - if error occurred while reloading the bundles.
